04/11/2008
PRISTINA, Kosovo -- The government adopted a bill Monday (November 3rd) on the country's budget for next year worth 1.43 billion euros. 
Minister for Economy and Finance Ahmet Shala said it will enable economic growth at a rate of 6%.
In other news Monday, Prime Minister Hashim Thaci reiterated the government's position that EULEX must be deployed across Kosovo without any conditions. 
He added "We will establish good neighbouring relations with all regional countries, including Serbia." (Koha Ditore, Zeri - 04/11/08; RTK, TV 21, Kohavision - 03/11/08)
